O-S (Oraxus Sports) Platform

1. Document Overview
1.1 Purpose
This Business Requirements Document (BRD) defines the functional and non-functional requirements for Oraxus Sports (O-S), a multi-sport tournament management and analytics platform available on web and mobile. The document outlines user roles, system capabilities, access control, and core business features.
1.2 Scope
The O-S platform enables users to:
Organize tournaments across multiple sports
Manage players, teams, matches, and statistics
View live scores and analytics
Communicate within sport-specific groups
Access premium features via paid subscriptions

2. Business Objectives
Provide a centralized platform for organizing and managing sports tournaments.
Support multiple sports with isolated data per sport.
Enable role-based access control for different user personas.
Offer free and premium plans with advanced analytics and AI insights.
Improve engagement through communication, notifications, and follow features.
Ensure scalability for future sports, analytics, and streaming integrations.

3. Supported Sports (Initial Release)
Cricket
Volleyball
Soccer
Pickleball
The system must be extensible to support additional sports in the future.

4. Platform Overview
4.1 Application Type
Web Application
Mobile Application (iOS & Android)
4.2 User-Based System
Users can have multiple roles
Users can associate with one or more sports
Sport context is isolated (data and views are sport-specific)

5. User Roles & Permissions
5.1 Platform Admin / Super Admin
Description:
System-level administrators with full control over the platform.
Permissions:
Full CRUD access to:
Users
Roles and permissions
Sports
Teams, players, tournaments, matches
Assign and revoke user roles
Manage subscription plans and payments
View and manage platform-wide analytics
Moderate content and user activity
One or more Super Admins are created by default during system initialization.

5.2 Viewer (Default User Role)
Permissions:
Create, update, and deactivate own profile
View:
Teams
Tournaments
Player profiles
Match statistics
Live scores
Streaming content (if available)
Follow:
Players (within selected sport)
Teams
Tournaments

5.3 Player
Includes all Viewer permissions plus:
Create and manage player profiles per sport
View basic statistics
Send and receive:
Team joining requests
Tournament participation requests
Receive notifications for approvals and updates

5.4 Premium User (Paid Subscription)
Includes all Player permissions plus:
Access to detailed statistics
AI-powered analytics
Player comparison across multiple players
Advanced performance insights and trends

5.5 Official (Team Owner / Manager)
Permissions:
CRUD operations on Teams
Manage team players
Send and receive tournament joining requests
Respond to player joining requests
Receive notifications for approvals and updates

5.6 Organizer
Description:
User who creates and manages tournaments.
Permissions:
CRUD operations on Tournaments
Schedule matches
Manage tournament details
Send and receive:
Team joining requests
Player joining requests
Approve or reject participation requests
Receive notifications for tournament-related events

6. Core Functional Requirements
6.1 User Management
User registration and authentication
Role assignment and role switching (if applicable)
Profile management
Account deactivation

6.2 Sport Selection & Context Switching
Default sport is selected upon login
Users can switch sports from a dropdown/list
All data views update based on selected sport

6.3 Tournament Management
Create, update, delete tournaments
Assign sport, format, and rules
Manage schedules and matches
Track tournament status

6.4 Team Management
Create and manage teams
Add/remove players
Handle team participation requests

6.5 Player Management
Player profiles per sport
Basic and advanced statistics tracking
Performance history

6.6 Statistics & Analytics
Sport-specific statistics
Live match updates
AI-driven insights (Premium users)
Player comparison tools

6.7 Communication & Notifications
Group-based communication per sport
Direct user-to-user messaging (optional)
System notifications for:
Requests
Approvals
Match updates
Tournament events

6.8 Payments & Subscriptions
Free and Paid subscription models
Integration with payment gateway
Subscription management
Access control based on plan

7. Non-Functional Requirements
7.1 Performance
Support concurrent users and live match updates
Low-latency communication and notifications
7.2 Security
Secure authentication and authorization
Role-based access control
Data isolation per sport
Secure payment processing
7.3 Scalability
Ability to add new sports
Handle growing user base and tournaments
7.4 Availability
High availability for live scoring and tournaments
Mobile and web parity in features

8. Assumptions
Users may have multiple roles simultaneously
Statistics and analytics vary by sport
Live streaming integration may depend on third-party services

9. Out of Scope (Initial Phase)
Betting or gambling features
Fantasy league features
Offline access

10. Success Metrics
User engagement per sport
Tournament creation and participation rates
Conversion from free to premium users
System performance during live events
